cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper focuses on automated hyperparameter optimization using sequential model-based optimization, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a transfer learning approach to speed up the optimization process, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments also involve computer vision datasets, which suggests the paper may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The proposed algorithm involves neural networks, which suggests the paper may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves optimization, which suggests the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
